
--------------------------------------------------------
	makemySDSS suite 

For downloading SDSS Fields and generating PSF from them.


Fabricio Ferrari, www.ferrari.pro.br, 2013
--------------------------------------------------------

NEEDS

- read_PSF executable from the SDSS 
(http://www.sdss.org/dr7/products/images/read_psf.html)
- astLib python library to transform WCS to PIXEL



HOWTO.

[1]. Have a list with objects (header optional), say named foo.list

objid,ra,dec,run,rerun,camcol,field
587725576423342343,257.91582337,64.10728627,1356,40,2,32
587725576423342340,257.93428764,64.11213814,1356,40,2,32
587725576423276790,258.03445697,64.28134959,1356,40,2,31
587725576423276784,257.99694569,64.27669727,1356,40,2,31
587725576423342219,258.0041133,64.03787358,1356,40,2,32
...


[2]. run the makemySDSSlist.py  in it (makemySDSSlist.py LISTFILE FILTERS)

$   python makemySDSSlist.py  foo.list ugriz   >  download.sh

this will generate the  download scritp to all the fields where this objects are.



[3]. Run the download script

$  sh download.sh

it will download  and store the files 
in directories  sdss_u,  sdss_g,  and so on.


[4]. run the makemyPSF.py on the same list with same filters.

$  python makemyPSF foo.list ugriz

it will download the psField files to psField directory, then will locate each 
object from the list in pixel coordinates in a given field and then will 
reconstruct the PSF fits file for it from the information in the psField file 
relative to the Field in question.


[5]. write me saying everything went ok and thanks.


